        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>107 Mac Dougal St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                <date>3d June/59</date>
            </p>
            <p>Rev Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The committee of ar<lb/>rangements at <placeName>St.
                    Louis</placeName> have<lb/> invited me to consecrate their<lb/> Synagogue &amp;
                I have accepted<lb/> the invitation. This morning I<lb/> receive a letter from them dated<lb/>
                <date>31<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date> Ulto. In which they say to me<lb/> that they
                    <sic>inclose</sic> “the 'order<lb/> of service' not having any<lb/> one here
                capable of translating<lb/> them, would solicit you to<lb/> translate and have them
                printed<lb/> on one side Hebrew and on the<lb/> other side English—there being<lb/>
                a number of German members<lb/> of our congregation it is likewise<lb/> desired that
                some be printed<lb/> in the Hebrew and German languages.<lb/> The whole number to be
                printed<lb/> is 600 copies say 500 Heb &amp; Engl.<lb/> and 100 Heb. &amp; Germ. It
                is also</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>suggested that the printing be<lb/> awarded to the <persName>Rev Isaac
                    Leeser</persName><lb/> &amp; that when done they be forwarded<lb/> here by
                express with <persName>Billy</persName> for paymt.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In compliance with their<lb/> suggestion, you will oblige me<lb/> by
                letting me know whether you<lb/> will undertake the printing<lb/> &amp; engage to
                have the 600 copies<lb/> delivered at <placeName>St. Louis</placeName> on or before<lb/>
                <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June</date>. It will make about<lb/> 14 pages,
                including the Title. I<lb/> should also like to know if you<lb/> prefer the German
                translation<lb/> in this sort of writing or in<lb/> German text. The folks at<lb/>
                <placeName>St. Louis</placeName> do not say how they<lb/> wish their German printed
                so<lb/> you must exercise your own<lb/> discretion, &amp; use that sort of<lb/> type
                which you have most<lb/> readily at hand.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As I fear your reply</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>by post will not reach me<lb/> till <date>Tuesday</date> morning, and I should<lb/>
                like to send you the manuscript<lb/> by <date>Monday</date> afternoon mail<lb/>
                please reply to my questions<lb/> by Telegraph, as soon after<lb/> receipt of this
                as <add>שבת</add> will<lb/> permit</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Wishing you <add>שמחת יום טוב</add><lb/> I am Rev Dr. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours very respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">M J Raphall Dr.</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
